Master of Engineering (M.E.) – Higher Degree Programmes

The ME programmes of 2 years of normal duration are uniquely designed and structured for Engineers who are employed professionals or in the pursuit of seeking employment. These programmes give an immersive professional experience and an opportunity to acquire further competence either in one’s own discipline or gain complementary knowledge in Engineering as well as Interdisciplinary areas to upgrade their career.

Some of the features of the programmes are:

Evenings and/or weekend classes.

Flexibility in the pace and duration of programmes for the convenience of working professionals.

The requirements of these programmes are described in terms of the total number of units which a student must complete rather than the duration. However, most students may be able to complete such a programme in two years.

M.E. Design Engineering

The M.E. Design Engineering programme aims at equipping a Mechanical Engineer with the core competency skills required to be a Design Engineer. The programme primarily covers the broad areas namely: Materials Technology, Product Design, Mechanisms and Robotics, Computer Aided tools for a Mechanical Engineering Analysis and Design in addition to discipline-based elective courses in emerging & advanced areas.

M.E. Electrical with specialization in Power Electronics and Drives

This programme has been duly approved for offering by the Knowledge and Human Development Authority (KHDA), Government of Dubai. With a specialization in Power Electronics and Drives, the students will be well-versed in the operation, function and interaction between various components and subsystems used in power electronic converters, electric machines and adjustable-speed drives. Through this programme, a student can be gainfully employed in manufacturing, construction and power distribution industries.

M.E. Microelectronics

The M.E. Microelectronics programme aims at offering courses that provide the necessary skill set required by microelectronics design engineers to find ways to deliver smaller, faster, and cheaper devices that are in-line with the current technological developments. The programme primarily covers the broad areas namely, Modeling of Microelectronic Devices, IC Fabrication Technology, VLSI Architecture and Design, CAD tools for Analog and Digital IC Design in addition to discipline based elective courses in emerging & advanced areas.

M.E. Software Systems

The programme incorporates core & elective courses along with Practice School (PS)/Dissertation that equip students to cater to the dynamic needs of the software industry. The students acquire a strong foundation on the recent trends and technologies in the field of computer science like Machine Learning, Data Analytics, Cyber Security among others. The Practice School is a formal method of bringing the reality of the professional environment into the educational process. 

M.E. Civil Engineering with specialization in Infrastructure Engineering and Management

M.E. Civil with specialization in Infrastructure Engineering & Management program includes the design, planning, construction, maintenance and management frameworks of various infrastructures across different sectors in Civil Engineering. This programme develops the advanced technical knowledge in infrastructure engineering within the economic, sustainability and environmental context. The successful completion of the course helps the candidate to create new infrastructures as well as to manage the existing infrastructure systems.

Master of Business Administration (M.B.A.)

The MBA programme at BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus aimed for graduates across various disciplines, working professionals and entrepreneurs offers core management courses with specialized electives focussing on real-world industry practice. Students graduating with this MBA degree acquire a dynamic ability to apply methodical, technical and innovative thought processes to business problems in their respective fields.

Some of the features of the programmes are:

Evenings and/or weekend classes.

Flexibility in the pace and duration of programmes for the convenience of working professionals.

The requirements of these programmes are described in terms of the total number of units which a student must complete rather than the duration. However, most students are able to complete such a programme in two years duration.

This programme will develop your business sensitivity through experiential and professional learning to provide you with the right platform for your career advancement.

Gain an internationally recognised MBA with BITS Pilani, Dubai and get access to connect & engage with experienced cohorts to widen your perspective. The flexible & modular curriculum allows one to learn while you earn. Synchronously provides opportunities to fresh graduates to build global business skills and prepare themselves for leadership roles.



Master’s Degree in Electrical 

M.E. Electrical (with specialization in Power Electronics and Drives)

It is well known that Electrical Engineers have a dominant role in the development of a country’s infrastructure. With Dubai hosting the 2020 World Expo and with the growing opportunities for engineers in the UAE and Gulf countries, BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus is now enhancing its offerings by introducing the M.E. Electrical with specialization in Power Electronics and Drives programme from the academic year 2018-19. This programme has been duly approved for offering by the Knowledge and Human Development Authority (KHDA), Government of Dubai.

With a specialization in Power Electronics and Drives, the students will be well-versed in the operation, function and interaction between various components and sub-systems used in power electronic converters, electric machines and adjustable-speed drives. They will also will be able to build up sound knowledge in the areas of interaction of power devices with power systems as well as the control aspects of power electronic activities. This would help them to pursue a career as Design and Maintenance Engineers in the field of power converter-based systems used for conversion and processing of electric energy. They will also become employable as Field or Testing Engineers dealing with power electronic components, converters, and specialized functions of power systems. They can be gainfully employed in manufacturing, construction and power distribution industries. Especially they will be able to contribute more, functionally in the areas of M.E.P (Mechanical, Electrical and Plumbing) and H.V.A.C (Heating Ventilation and Air Conditioning) in the concerned organizations in Gulf countries, leading to overall infrastructural developments of the whole GCC.

The M.E. programme in Electrical with specialization in Power Electronics and Drives is normally of two years duration (4 semesters).

Master’s Degree in Software Systems 

Master’s Degree in Software Systems

The curriculum of the programme incorporates core & elective courses along with Practice School (PS) / Dissertation that equip students to cater to the dynamic needs of the software industry. The core and the elective courses enable students to acquire strong foundation on the recent trends and technologies in the field of computer science like Machine Learning, Data Analytics, Cyber Security among others.The Practice School is a formal method of bringing the reality of professional environment into the educational process. We believe that with a well formed curriculum and persistent mentoring from diligent faculty our students will be innovative thinkers, problem solvers and entrepreneurs.

M.E. Microelectronics

Master’s Degree in Microelectronics

Microelectronics is a field related to  study and micro fabrication of electronic components which help miniaturizing the size of electronic circuits and systems made from semiconductors. Many components of normal electronic design such as transistors, capacitors etc., have their microelectronic equivalent. They are employed in today's chip technologies  that accommodate analog, digital and mixed signal circuits on micro-dimensional semiconductor wafers. As techniques improve, the scale of microelectronic  components continue to decrease. At smaller scales, the relative impact of  intrinsic circuit properties such as interconnections (called the parasitic effects) may become more significant. The M.E. Microelectronics programme aims at offering courses that provide necessary skill set required by microelectronics design engineer to find ways to compensate for or to minimize these effects, while always delivering smaller, faster, and cheaper devices in line with the current technological developments.  

The M.E. Microelectronics programme primarily covers the broad areas namely Modeling of Microelectronic Devices, IC Fabrication Technology, VLSI Architecture and Design, CAD tools for Analog and Digital IC Design in addition to discipline based elective courses in emerging & advanced areas.  

Master’s Degree in Design Engineering 

Master’s Degree in Design Engineering

Design Engineering is a generic term that covers multiple engineering disciplines including but not limited to  mechanical engineering. It deals with a branch of study that sets a direction to the design effort needed for most complex parts of design. A design engineer usually leads the project, designing the overall framework and the most far reaching parts. He/She also directs the designers/drafters on sub-system designs of a project's more routine parts as necessary through prototyping, engineering drawings, production, CAD, etc. In collaboration with industrial designers and marketing professionals, he/she develops the product concept and specifications and directs the design effort from that point. Products are generally  designed with input from a number of sources such as manufacturing, purchasing, tool making and package engineering.  

The M.E. Design Engineering programme aims at equipping a Mechanical Engineer with the core competency skills required to be a Design Engineer. The programme primarily covers the broad areas namely: Materials Technology, Product Design, Mechanisms and Robotics, Computer Aided tools for a Mechanical Engineering Analysis and Design in addition to discipline based elective courses in emerging & advanced areas.  

Eligibility Criteria For Higher Degree Programmes (M.E.)

The following eligibility criteria is applicable for admission to BITS Pilani, Dubai Campus. A candidate seeking admission to a particular programme has to meet the eligibility criteria for that programme as given below:

Eligibility criteria for admission to Higher Degree Programmes

A minimum aggregate of 60% in the qualifying degree as indicated below for each programme.

 

M.E. Design: B.E./B.Tech. in Mechanical Engineering or its equivalent.

M.E. Electrical (Power Electronics & Drive): B.E./B.Tech. in EEE, E&I or ECE or its equivalent.

M.E. Microelectronics: B.E./B.Tech. in EEE/E&I/ECE/CS or M.Sc. Physics or its equivalent.

M.E. Software Systems: B.E./B.Tech./M.Sc./M.C.A or equivalent.

M.E. Civil (Infrastructure Engg. & Mgmt.) : B.E./B.Tech. in Civil Engineering or its equivalent. (B.E. Mechanical & Electrical may also be considered with some deficiency courses)

 

Candidates who meet the above criteria will be required to appear and successfully clear the Aptitude test/Interview to qualify for admission.

Refund Policy

One-Time fee: 

Application fee and Admission Fee are non-refundable.

Activity fee is fully refundable if the student withdraws before the date of registration. If the student withdraws within four weeks from the date of registration, whether the student registers or not, 75% of the Activity fee is refundable. If the student withdraws after four weeks from the date of registration, the entire Activity fee is non-refundable.

Tuition Fee: 

If a student accepts the admission offer and completes the admission formalities but withdraws before the date of registration, 80% of the first installment of first semester tuition fee is refundable.

If a student withdraws within one week of the date of registration irrespective of whether the student registers or not, 50% of the first installment of first semester tuition fee is refundable.

If a student withdraws after one week of the date of registration irrespective of whether the student registers or not, the first installment of first semester tuition fee is non- refundable.

Hostel Fee: 

If a student opts not to avail the hostel facility after paying the hostel fee and if the request for the same is received before the commencement of the semester, 90% of the semester’s hostel fee and facility fee is refundable.

If request for not availing the hostel facility is received within one week of the commencement of the semester, 50% of the semester’s hostel fee and facility fee is refundable.

If request for not availing the hostel facility is received after one week of the commencement of the semester, the entire first semester’s hostel fee and facility fee is non-refundable.

Visa and Medical Insurance fee: 

Visa fee and Medical Insurance fee is non-refundable, if the same has been applied.

Transport Fee: 

If a student opts not to avail the transport facility after paying the transport fee and if the request for the same is received before the commencement of the semester, 90% of the semester’s transport fee paid is refundable.

If request for not availing the transport facility is received within two weeks of the commencement of the semester, 50% of the semester’s transport fee is refundable.

If request for not availing the transport facility is received after two weeks of the commencement of the semester, the entire first semester’s transport fee is non refundable.

Note: All refunds will take a minimum of 4 weeks from the date of withdrawal.

Group Concession for Corporate Executives: Three or more candidates from the same organization seeking admission into any higher degree programme in any semester of the academic year 2023-24 would be eligible for a 10% concession on the tuition fee for the normal duration of the programme subject to continuance of the degree programme by all candidates.
